!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

decision /dɪˈsɪʒən/

(decisions) 

1. N-COUNT When you make a decision , you choose what should be done or which is the best of various possible actions. 决定 

例： I don't want to make the wrong decision and regret it later. 我不想作出错误的决定，以后后悔。 

2. N-UNCOUNT Decision is the act of deciding something or the need to decide something. 作决定 

例： The growing pressures of the crisis may mean that the moment of decision can't be too long delayed. 这次危机不断增长的压力可能意味着作决定的时刻不会拖延很久。 

3. N-UNCOUNT Decision is the ability to decide quickly and definitely what to do. 果断 

例： He is very quick-thinking and very much a man of decision. 他思维很敏捷，是个很果断的人。

</div>

